<br>
A proc is nice and all, but it is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> impractical</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to try to consider it in a fight.  I'm not saying it isn't good.  I'm not saying it isn't useful or helpful or that it doesn't increase the DPS... I'm saying it isn't practical to consider it in your DPS during a fight.  In theory, a proc weapon would need to proc X amount of times to reach that 6%, I'd rather ignore that &quot;possibility&quot; when I'm fighting.  Theories and the application of theories in &quot;the real world&quot; are too different things.<br>
<br>
37/36 is a better ratio than 29/30.  Yes it'll be times when your DPS will fluctuate, but you are more likely to hit your average DPS with that, then counting on X number of procs.<br>
<br>
As for a DT weapon... of course!  I'd be praying for a proc every fight!  More then likely, every proc will happen at the end of the fight just to piss me off anyway.... <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=281768>Tettsuo Otomo</a> 59 Grasshopper of the Celestial Fist<br>
